or by group of persons.</SPAN><SPAN \r\ndir=rtl></SPAN><SPAN dir=rtl></SPAN><SPAN dir=rtl \r\nstyle="FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Times New Roman''; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: Verdana"><SPAN \r\ndir=rtl></SPAN><SPAN dir=rtl></SPAN> </SPAN></FONT></SPAN>\r\n<LI><SPAN \r\nstyle="FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman''">Management \r\nof access doors.</SPAN> \r\n<LI><SPAN \r\nstyle="FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman''">Controllers \r\nmanagement.</SPAN> \r\n<LI><SPAN \r\nstyle="FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman''">Access \r\ncards management.</SPAN> \r\n<LI><SPAN \r\nstyle="FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman''">Affectation \r\nof access cards to people</SPAN> \r\n<LI><SPAN \r\nstyle="FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman''">Real-time \r\nshow of the map of local or distant site.</SPAN> \r\n<LI><SPAN \r\nstyle="FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman''">Edition \r\nof multi-criterion states.</SPAN> \r\n<LI><SPAN \r\nstyle="FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman''">Real \r\ntime localization of people for a given site.</SPAN> \r\n<LI><SPAN \r\nstyle="FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman''">Automatic \r\nclose of all doors in case of parameterized needs or by a simple mouse \r\nclick.</SPAN> \r\n<LI><SPAN \r\nstyle="FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman''"></SPAN><SPAN \r\nstyle="FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman''">tracing \r\npeople movements by period.</SPAN> \r\n<LI><SPAN \r\nstyle="FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman''"></SPAN><SPAN \r\nstyle="FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman''">File \r\ninformer.</SPAN></LI></UL>\r\n<P><SPAN \r\nstyle="FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman''"><FONT \r\ncolor=coral><STRONG><U>controllers and sub \r\nterminals</U></STRONG></FONT></SPAN></P>\r\n<P><SPAN \r\nstyle="FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: FR; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman''"><FONT \r\ncolor=#ff7f50><FONT color=black>The new </FONT><U><FONT color=blue>B-Net 92 50 \r\nAccess Control Manager</FONT></U><FONT color=black> with its compact design is \r\nespecially suitable for small access solutions. It controls up to four doors and \r\nis compatible with the Bedanet 92 90 Access \r\nManager</FONT>.</FONT></SPAN></P></FONT></TD></TR></TBODY></TABLE>\r\n<P>Depending on the requirements both controls complement one another and form \r\nan integrated solution. The B-Net 92 50 has its own decision making logic, \r\nchecks and decides autonomously whether access is granted or not.<BR>The control \r\nunit can additionally be expanded by AVISO routines. In this way, further \r\ncomponents for building management can be easily connected.<BR>The new <U><FONT \r\ncolor=#0000ff>Bedanet 92 90 Access Control Manager</FONT></U> will allow \r\nintegration of the entire Kaba Benzing product spectrum into one homogeneous \r\nsolution, and ensure compatibility with future <STRONG>Access Control</STRONG> \r\nproducts. Because of its decision making logic and plausibility checks, the \r\nBedanet<BR>92 90 is highly autonomous. Its features allow for the flexible \r\nimplementation of every security concept.<BR></P>\r\n<P>The <U><FONT color=#0000ff>Bedanet 92 20</FONT></U> for <STRONG>Access \r\nControl</STRONG> effectively protect your facilities from unauthorized access, \r\nboth online and offline. All personnel and time data necessary for authorization \r\ncheck is stored in the devices.</P></TD></TR></TBODY></TABLE></DIV>\r\n<BLOCKQUOTE dir=ltr style="MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px">\r\n<BLOCKQUOTE dir=ltr style="MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px">\r\n<BLOCKQUOTE dir=ltr style="MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px">\r\n<P>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The intelligent terminals decide, whether access is granted \r\nor denied. Sabotage attempts&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; and&nbsp;manipulations are \r\ntransmitted with the standard sabotage contact to the superior unit.<BR></P>\r\n<P>With the <FONT color=blue><U>Bedanet 90 20</U></FONT>, Kaba Benzing has a \r\nuniversally applicable digital input/output module (I/O module) designed for \r\nAccess Control.</P>\r\n<P>In an access system, this module extends the performance range of the B-Net \r\n92 50 and Bedanet 92 90 controls with additional door opening and monitoring \r\nfunctions. The Bedanet 90 20 features 2 digital outputs, e.g. for door-opener \r\nrelays, beepers, lights, etc. It also has 8 digital inputs, e.g. to connect \r\ndoor-opener push buttons, door frame contacts, bolt contacts, or pass-through \r\ncontacts. The two RS485 interfaces are used to connect the control unit and the \r\nup to 2 Bedanet 91 04 / 91 05 subterminals.<BR></P>\r\n<P>The <U><FONT color=#0000ff>Bedanet 91 04, 91 05, and 91 20 \r\nsubterminals</FONT></U> have no active elements like a relay for door-opening \r\ne.g. They only serve as capturing units that forward information to the superior \r\nunit in the protected area. For single door solutions or gates, a subterminal is \r\nconnected to the control <U><FONT color=#0000ff>Bedanet 92 20 S</FONT></U>.</P>\r\n<P>The latest solution for Access Control is the <U><FONT \r\ncolor=#0000ff>biometric terminal Bedanet 91 20 Fingerprint</FONT></U>. The \r\nunique biometric data in the employee''s fingerprint is recorded along with their \r\npersonnel number and stored in the Bedanet 91 20 Fingerprint terminals. \r\nAdvantages of biometric identification methods - Because biometric traits are \r\nunique to each individual, they can be used to prevent theft or fraud. Unlike a \r\npassword or PIN (personal identification number), a biometric trait cannot be \r\nforgotten, lost, or stolen.<BR></P>\r\n<P>Another innovation in the sector of authorization systems is the <U><FONT \r\ncolor=#0000ff>PCR 05 LEGIC PC reader</FONT></U>. It records badge informations \r\nand is also used for authorization assignment. Connected directly to the PC, \r\nthis reader allows to personalize processes at the computer.&nbsp;The PC is \r\nactivated as long as an authorized LEGIC medium is within the read area. If \r\nsomeone unauthorized is trying to end the application, Windows is automatically \r\nterminated.<BR></P>\r\n<P><BR>&nbsp;</P></BLOCKQUOTE></BLOCKQUOTE></BLOCKQUOTE>', 1, 'DOCUMENT', '');
